<section xml:id="S_products">
  <title>Functions Arising from the Products of Two Lines</title>

  <introduction>
    <p>
      You have likely noticed that we are now investigating a new type of function. The graphs have an obvious curve to them; they are not straight lines. As you investigate products of linear functions, think about <xref text="title" ref="act-batty-func"/> and what you remember about non-linear functions from your previous work in mathematics courses.
    </p>
  </introduction>

  <worksheet xml:id="act-invest-prods">
    <title>Investigating Products of Linear Functions</title>
    
    <introduction>
      <p>
        Solve the problems that follow to investigate the appearance of products of linear functions. Think about these questions as you work: To what family of functions do products of linear functions belong? What shape is the graph of this function family? (Note: For a review of function notation, please see <xref ref="function-notation"/>)
      </p>
    </introduction>

